ial/TwinParadox/Basic.html#SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox\">InstantaneousTwinParadox</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The twin paradox in which:\n- Twin A starts at `0` and travels at constant\n  speed to `[15, 0, 0, 0]`.\n- Twin B starts at `0` and travels at constant speed to\n  `[7.5, 6, 0, 0]` and then at (different) constant speed to `[15, 0, 0, 0]`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Special/TwinParadox/Basic.html#SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox.example1","kind":"def","line":78,"name":"SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox.example1","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L78-L117"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Special/TwinParadox/Basic.html#SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox.ageGap_nonneg\"><span class=\"name\">SpecialRelativity</span>.<span class=\"name\">InstantaneousTwinParadox</span>.<span class=\"name\">ageGap_nonneg</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Meta/Informal/Basic.html#InformalLemma\">InformalLemma</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"In the twin paradox with instantaneous acceleration, Twin A is always older\nthen Twin B. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Relativity/Special/TwinParadox/Basic.html#SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox.ageGap_nonneg","kind":"def","line":66,"name":"SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox.ageGap_nonneg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L66-L70"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Relativity/Special/TwinParadox/Basic.html#SpecialRelativity.InstantaneousTwinParadox.ageGap\"><span class=\"name\">SpecialRelativity</span>.<span class=\"name\">InstantaneousTwinParadox</span>.<span class=\"name\">ageGap</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<spa